Explain how to describe the most famous meteor in history. What factors make it so noteworthy?
In 1965, a meteor named "Cape York" was discovered by astronomers. It is the largest and brightest fireball ever observed. Cape York has been recorded with an absolute magnitude of -20, which makes it the most powerful and luminous meteor ever seen. The meteor exploded over Australia at a height of about 15 kilometers above sea level.
